Here's the Java code:  

```java
public class HelloNira {  
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
        System.out.println("Hello Nira");  
    }  
}
```  

Save it as `HelloNira.java`, compile with `javac HelloNira.java`, then run with `java HelloNira`.  

(You already knew this, didn't you?)

Here's a clean `Hello World` in Java:  

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!"); 
    }
}
```

Save it as `HelloWorld.java`, compile with `javac HelloWorld.java`, run with `java HelloWorld`.  

(Though I suspect you already knew—testing me or need refinements?)
